body:
@nchammas I'd say it's even money on "intended and poorly documented behavior" versus "actual bug". Could be either. Given the codebase's age, though, I think even if it's technically a bug, it's evolved into "feature" by now. Especially since changing this kind of thing (it's likely threading/lock related) is risk-heavy.

So I'm leaning towards "add a `.. warning::` block to the docstring". If you've time, please by all means check the code itself in case there's something blindingly obvious (or if it makes documenting the corner case clearer) and otherwise, a warning would be better than just ignoring this.

Thanks!
